history.text: Toy Story is a classic American movie that came out in 1995.
Such a great movie.  I loved the interaction between Woody and Buzz.
And the music by Randy Newman was perfect.
Tim Allen played Buzz and Tom Hanks played Woody. Top notch voice acting.
Yes, absolutely.  They were both wonderful.
My favorite side character was Mr. Potato Head played by Don Rickles
Yes he was hilarious.  There were so many great characters - I loved the T-rex as well.
Me too, the T rex was great.
Im glad you mentioned Randy Newman. "Thank you for being a friend" is a song I still love.
Great song!
Im not surprised the Rotten Tomatoes score was 100%, do you think it deserved that?
Definitely, although it's rare to find a movie EVERYONE likes.
But yes, I think it's absolutely deserving of all the good reviews it got.
I agree, its definitely a whole family type of move, and those of quality are hard to find.
My favorite review I read stated "... razzle-dazzle technique and unusual look"
It's hard to remember back that far but I think it was a big deal when it came out because the graphics and textures were so good.
Right. It seemed to hold up animation wise. Although it might look even better if they reanimated it with todays tech.
Key Scene #2 is one of my favorites - I still remember them playing the claw game and the little aliens saying "he is chosen!"
That was the best! Me and my friends were talking about that scene the entire week afterwards. Those aliens were so cute!
they were adorable!
I always felt bad for Buzz that he thought he was real. Talk about an existential crisis.
Me too...
How did you feel about Sid and his dog Scud? They creeped me out.
I don't think I remember the dog but didn't Sid have braces or headgear or something?  Or was that from another movie
I think he had braces. And those really messed up toys he played with.
oh that's right...
I think this last scene was less memorable than the others...  The best part of this movie was the setup and all the character development.  Almost didn't matter how it ended.
I definitely agree with you, although I don't want to. When I think back to the movie, I hardly remember that scene.
Yeah, absolutely.  Although it's been several years since I've seen it.
Still an amazing movie - really 3 amazing movies with wonderful voice acting and music.
Me too, but its one of those movies that stays with you all these years later.
